            "SummaryExplanation": {
                "val": "The decrease in FY 2021 from the previous President's Budget submission is due to:\n(1) a realignment of funds to PE 0603160BR (Counter Weapons of Mass Destruction Advanced Technology Development) to increase investment in WMD counterterrorism activities, and \n(2) Defense-Wide Review (DWR) adjustment of -$31.970 million resulting from reductions to DTRA's lowest priority RDT&E programs and the the transfer of C-IED programs to the Army to better align RDT&E efforts with the C-IED mission holder.  The Army assumes executive agent responsibilities for C-IED effective 1 October 2020."
            }
        },
